<div><h3>PHYS 251 - Statistical Physics </h3>  <hr>This is an introductory course on statistical mechanics which starts with ensemble theory and ends with an introduction to critical phenomena. Starting from probability theory, we will derive relations between microscopic and macroscopic properties of a system. We will review basic thermodynamics and study its statistical interpretation. Methods of statistical mechanics will be used to develop Bose-Einstein and Fermi-Dirac statistics. During the second half of the semester, selected topics will be approached numerically and students will use computer simulations to study more complex, yet more realistic, systems.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=28&coid=93896" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=93896&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=93896&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt1056" target="_blank">PHYS 150</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span>, <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=28&coid=94331" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=94331&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=94331&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt7191" target="_blank">PHYS 127</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> &amp; <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=28&coid=93894" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=93894&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=93894&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt8487" target="_blank">PHYS 131</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> <br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Spring<br><br><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt1056"></div><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt7191"></div><d